But wait - the main agent still works because yoagent might resolve the API key from environment in the provider layer. For OpenAI-compatible providers, the `OpenAiCompatProvider` might look up the env var. But the `SubAgentTool` creates its own provider instance (line 1406-1411) with the API key passed explicitly - if it's empty, the sub-agent fails.

The fix: In `build_sub_agent_tool`, if `config.api_key` is empty, try to resolve it from the environment (using `provider_api_key_env`) before passing it to the sub-agent.

